LibriVox recording of The Dwarf's Chamber And Other Stories by Fergus Hume.
Read in English by David Wales

Short Stories by Fergus Hume (1859 – 1932), a prolific English novelist. - Summary by wikipedia

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

title: The Dwarf's Chamber And Other Stories

reviews.reviewbody:
I really enjoyed this collection of stories.  The dwarf's chamber really reflects the different perspective of people then and now, while also solving a neat mystery.  

The rest of the stories are likewise excellent.  

Reading was fine, recordings were also fine.

The author's repeated insistence that these tales prove that "truth is stranger than fiction" sounds quite silly given the unrealistic premises of his stories. These tales are quite fantastic but still engaging. Rollicking yarns, as it were. Not great stories, but good.

The reading is mostly clear and audible. In one story however, the narrator attempts a strong cockney accent. To me it sounds like someone whose tongue is numb from the dentist. I couldn't make out the words. Unfortunate.
